      dct:source narr:Sample_LandingPageScrollDriven_20260704 ;
      skos:note "Scarlet's core reframe (Jul 4): the current landing page fails by mode, not by content — it explains the product instead of demonstrating it. The fix is to shift from telling to showing: primary source material plus brief commentary and framing. Stated as a settled conclusion (delivery: measured and settled, 2.0 w/s, energy below baseline, conf 0.96)." .

    narr:Claim_ScrollDrivenAnimationMechanism a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_ScrollDrivenLandingPage ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_LandingPageScrollDriven_20260704 ;
      skos:note "The mechanism: a curated scroll-driven animation (popularised by NYT Snowfall) where scrolling drives the full pipeline visually. Beats: (1) typed user message; (2) conversations flow in as labeled boxes; (3) each conversation breaks into symbol particles that form a network; (4) network feeds AI thinking; (5) nodes descend as provenance footnotes; (6) generated response mostly transparent, a few statements at full opacity; (7) hover footnote draws provenance line into graph; (8) perspective load-and-expand shown; (9) 'something's missing' → introspect → gap shown; (10) voice memo ingestion → directional vectors → transaction enters graph; (11) GitHub branch/PR review; (12) sharing/deployment with phone agent. Idea arrived as the generative moment of the memo (delivery: 4.7 w/s, fast and fluent)." .

    narr:Claim_PersonasNotSeparateScenarios a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:Narrative_ScrollDrivenLandingPage ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_LandingPageScrollDriven_20260704 ;
      skos:note "Personas are NOT separate scenarios or a selector: 'we just want to make sure there's points in this where any of those personas can see themselves.' Each beat gets at most a couple sentences of commentary — more importantly how it's unique and different from other ways of doing this — with links out to articles that go deeper on that particular moment." .

    narr:Claim_LandingPageContentCommentaryIA a narr:Claim ;
      narr:aboutNode narr:InformationArchitecture ;
      narr:hasConvictionLevel narr:Conviction_Boulder ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_LandingPageEpistemicArchitecture ;
      dct:source narr:Sample_LandingPageScrollDriven_20260704 ;
      skos:note "The landing page's IA is structured as: primary source material (what is actually happening) + commentary and framing (briefly). This is the same structure as a memory itself. The product's own epistemics become the page's information architecture — a self-demonstrating design principle." .

